                          June 15 (Bloomberg) -- CBOE Holdings Inc., the last major U.S. securities exchange owned by its members, completed its transformation into a public company with an initial public offering. The operator of the biggest options exchange raised $339 million selling 11.7 million shares at $29 after offering them at $27 to $29. The shares start trading today on the Nasdaq Stock Market under the ticker CBOE. Bloomberg's Suzanne O'Halloran reports. (Source: Bloomberg)  
                           

     
